---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const values = [
  { title: 'Zero Data Ingress', desc: 'We operate on a local-first model. No data ever leaves your device.' },
  { title: 'Privacy by Design', desc: 'Processing happens entirely in your browser memory—no logs, no databases.' },
  { title: 'Developer Velocity', desc: 'Tools built for speed, offline capability, and instant configuration parsing.' }
];
---

<Layout 
  title="About ConfigDev | Secure, Client-Side DevOps Tools"
  description="ConfigDev builds free, 100% client-side DevOps tools—crontab-to-systemd, PII scrubbing, CIDR subnetting—for engineers who need zero-upload utilities."
>
  <main id="main-content" class="w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    
    <header class="mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-neutral-900 tracking-tight mb-6">
        Building Secure Utilities for the Modern Infrastructure Stack
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        ConfigDev was founded on a simple premise: <strong>Developers shouldn't have to sacrifice security for convenience.</strong> In an era of cloud-connected tools, we provide a decentralized alternative that keeps your infrastructure secrets exactly where they belong—on your machine.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Core Security Architecture Section (SEO Anchor) -->
    <section class="mb-20 bg-neutral-900 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 text-white">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-6">Our Security Architecture</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          This site is <strong>fully client-based</strong>. We do not route your data to any server, database, or external backend infrastructure. 
        </p>
        <p>
          Every conversion, calculation, and transformation happens locally within your own browser’s memory (V8 engine). Because our tools run entirely on your device, your environment variables, production logs, and sensitive API keys never leave your machine. This guarantees 100% data privacy and compliance with the strictest corporate data governance mandates.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why Us Section -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-10">Why DevOps Engineers Choose ConfigDev</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        {values.map((item) => (
          <div class="border-t-4 border-amber-500 pt-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Mission Section -->
    <section class="border-t border-neutral-200 pt-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Our Mission</h2>
      <div class="text-neutral-600 space-y-4 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          We are streamlining the DevOps workflow by eliminating the "network round-trip" tax. Traditional SaaS tools force you to upload sensitive configuration files to third-party servers just to format JSON or mask PII strings. We believe that professional-grade tooling should be local, offline-capable, and private by default.
        </p>
        <p>
          Whether you are a Site Reliability Engineer (SRE) automating crontabs or a backend developer debugging environment payloads, ConfigDev provides the utility suite you need without the security risks you want to avoid.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="py-16">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-8">What We Build</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 mb-12">
      We engineer high-performance developer utilities that bridge the gap between complex infrastructure management and accessible web interfaces. Our focus is on building tools that simplify the mundane, high-risk tasks DevOps teams face every day.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <!-- Feature 1 -->
      <div class="p-6 border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl hover:border-amber-500 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Infrastructure Parsers</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
          Tools to validate, format, and convert complex configuration files (JSON, YAML, .env) with instant, local syntax feedback.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Feature 2 -->
      <div class="p-6 border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl hover:border-amber-500 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Security Utilities</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
          Browser-based log sanitizers and PII scrubbers that ensure sensitive production credentials stay off your clipboard and out of the cloud.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Feature 3 -->
      <div class="p-6 border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl hover:border-amber-500 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">DevOps Calculators</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
          Precision-engineered subnet mask calculators and cron-expression generators designed for rapid integration into your terminal workflow.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

  </main>
</Layout>